Description: Provides pseudo-weighting methods for finite-population
    inference from nonprobability samples using auxiliary information from
    one or more probability reference surveys. The package is based on the
    general estimating-equation framework of Landsman et al. (2026)
    <doi:10.1002/SIM.70403> for correcting participation bias. In the
    one-reference case, it implements the calibration estimator from this
    framework, and also supports the adjusted logistic propensity (ALP) method
    of Wang, Valliant, and Li (2021) <doi:10.1002/sim.9107> and the
    Chen-Li-Wu (CLW) method of Chen, Li, and Wu (2020)
    <doi:10.1080/01621459.2019.1677241> as related one-reference special
    cases. A central feature is the multiple-reference extension of the same
    framework, including cumulative pre-calibration and multi-reference
    calibration procedures for combining auxiliary information across
    reference surveys. Analytic variance estimation is based on Taylor
    linearization and accommodates complex reference-survey sampling designs
    through integration with the 'survey' package.
